From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Jan 2026 16:00:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] ipmi: kcs_bmc_gxp: add missing MODULE_LICENSE

The kcs_bmc_gxp module is missing the MODULE_LICENSE macro, causing
build failures with modpost error:

  FATAL: modpost: missing MODULE_LICENSE() in drivers/char/ipmi/kcs_bmc_gxp.o

Add MODULE_LICENSE("GPL") to fix the build.

Signed-off-by: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
---
 drivers/char/ipmi/kcs_bmc_gxp.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/char/ipmi/kcs_bmc_gxp.c b/drivers/char/ipmi/kcs_bmc_gxp.c
--- a/drivers/char/ipmi/kcs_bmc_gxp.c
+++ b/drivers/char/ipmi/kcs_bmc_gxp.c
@@ -217,3 +217,4 @@ module_platform_driver(gxp_kcs_bmc_driver);
 MODULE_AUTHOR("John Chung <john.chung@hpe.com>");
 MODULE_AUTHOR("Jorge Cisneros <jorge.cisneros@hpe.com>");
 MODULE_DESCRIPTION("HPE device interface to the KCS BMC device");
+MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");
